  "texts": [
    "In these conditions, the reliance on AI is not an expression of epistemic autonomy.",
    "It might be thought that individuals can exercise epistemic autonomy through their indirect reliance on the developers of ADDs, or the platforms that vouch for the reliability of these systems.",
    "I return to this point in the concluding section.",
    "For the present, it bears recalling that most ordinary individuals 7 Page 14 of 19 have little trust in the technology sector, and hence would be unlikely to identify with the developers of ADDs in this way.",
    "To further develop the argument that ADDs are likely to compromise the epistemic autonomy of many ordinary persons, it is worth comparing reliance on ADDs to the reliance on AI within a more familiar and more extensively theorized context."
